erver Tarleton Gillespie provides an overview of current social media practices and explains the underlying rationales for how, when, and why these policies are enforced. In doing so, Gillespie highlights that content moderation receives too little public scrutiny even as it is shapes social norms and creates consequences for public discourse, cultural production, and the fabric of society. Based on interviews with content moderators, creators, and consumers, this accessible, timely book is a must†'read for anyone who's ever clicked "like" or "retweet."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aSocial mediaxCensorship. 7aCOMPUTERS / Web / Social Media.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300235029423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/doc/cover/9780300235029.jpg  aGBV-deGruyter-alles